name: HOW THE NAKED AND FAMOUS GOT THEIR NAME.
description: Ever wonder how any band got their name? I do all the time. In the case of The Naked and Famous, we can specifically trace back their namesake through 2 other bands and their songs. Ready to go down a seemingly useless rabbit hole of a journey to music knowledge? Good me too. So our journey begins with the UK based Trip-Hop recording artist, Tricky. Tricky recorded a song in 1996 entitled, 'Tricky Kid' and within this track he might have referenced a song from the band The Presidents of The United States of America. They made a song in 1995 called 'Naked and Famous'. Either you absolutely love this one or now totally hate me for it. Either way, now you can't unsee it...you're welcome; my job is complete.
